# ============================================================================
# POTA, SOTA, WWFF
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# WWFF compliance note (Mario, DL4MFM / cqgma.org):
#
#   The GMA WWFF spot API is rate limited to 1 request/minute and 1440
#   requests/day per client. Mario has asked software authors to cache
#   spot data centrally rather than letting every installation poll
#   cqgma.org directly.
#
#   How OHB complies:
#     * The OHB runs fetch_wwff_cache.pl once per minute and
#       publishes the result at /ham/HamClock/ONTA/wwff_spots.json.
#     * When ALPHA_INSTALL is set to 'true', OHB gets the json
#       from cqgma.org directly.
#     * When ALPHA_INSTALL is set to a hostname, OHB gets the json
#       from http://$ALPHA_INSTALL/ham/HamClock/ONTA/wwff_spots.json.
#     * When ALPHA_INSTALL is set to a full URL, OHB gets the json
#       from that URL.
#     * When ALPHA_INSTALL is unset, it defaults to http://ohb.hamclock.app/ham/HamClock/ONTA/wwff_spots.json.
#
#
#   *** Self-install operators: Do not set ALPHA_INSTALL to true. ***
#   *** It is for the central mirror host only.         ***
#   the ALPHA_INSTALL= prefix can also be set:
#     $SCRIPTS/cron-wrapper.sh ALPHA_INSTALL=ohb.hamclock.app $SCRIPTS/fetch_wwff_cache.pl
# ============================================================================
*/2 * * * *    $SCRIPTS/cron-wrapper.sh $SCRIPTS/fetch_wwff_cache.pl
1-59/2 * * * * $SCRIPTS/cron-wrapper.sh $SCRIPTS/gen_onta.pl

0 3 * * 1      $SCRIPTS/cron-wrapper.sh $SCRIPTS/update_wwff_cache.pl
0 4 * * 1,4    $SCRIPTS/cron-wrapper.sh $SCRIPTS/update_sota_cache.pl
15 3 * * 0     $SCRIPTS/cron-wrapper.sh $SCRIPTS/update_pota_parks_cache.sh

1-56/5 * * * * $SCRIPTS/cron-wrapper.sh $SCRIPTS/gen_drap.sh

